{"TopicId":167158,"ForumId":44,"TopicTitle":"Serious Scientific Answers to Absurd Hypothetical questions","CreatedByName":"DAL59","CreatedById":180784,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-11-03T20:21:11Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"DAL59","CreatedById":180784,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-11-03T20:21:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBased on xkcd\u0027s What If(apparently inactive).\u00A0 Ask a absurd hypothetical question, and someone can come and give you a serious scientific answer.\u00A0\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Diche Bach","CreatedById":76097,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-11-04T12:49:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf the entire Surface Web (meaning everything that is not part of\u00A0the \u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Deep_web\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EDeep Web\u003C/a\u003E)\u00A0were to be archived:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n1. How much storage space would it occupy\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n2. How quickly would it need to be recorded to approach any semblance of an \u0022instantaneous\u0022 snapshot\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n3. How long would it take to transfer all of that content to print form\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n4. How many volumes of books would it fill?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBest I could come up with on short notice \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:wink:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"NSEP","CreatedById":165635,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-11-04T12:55:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223210763\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022167158\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221509799788\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002276097\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Diche Bach\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 minutes ago, Diche Bach said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf the entire Surface Web (meaning everything that is not part of\u00A0the \u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Deep_web\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EDeep Web\u003C/a\u003E)\u00A0were to be archived:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n1. How much storage space would it occupy\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n2. How quickly would it need to be recorded to approach any semblance of an \u0022instantaneous\u0022 snapshot\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n3. How long would it take to transfer all of that content to print form\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n4. How many volumes of books would it fill?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBest I could come up with on short notice \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:wink:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot answering the questions, but still, sorta related kinda?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022EkRFOXh.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022768\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/EkRFOXh.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Diche Bach","CreatedById":76097,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-11-04T13:00:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHa! I remember stumbling across a YT video on that topic of \u0022how much [some subset of human digitized information] weighs!\u0022 Not sure if it was the Internet or something more inclusive, but yeah . . . some seriously low-density stuff! . . . \u0022Light reading\u0022\u00A0 . . . Mere fluff . . . Lightweight marshmellow creme flimsy\u00A0 . . .\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Piatzin","CreatedById":166940,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-11-04T13:07:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you could magnetize the hull of a tank so that it had an extremely negative charge, and somehow magnetized incoming bullets so that they acquired a similar negative charge, would this essentially create a sort of repelling-thingy force shield?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe like charges would repel, and the bullets would slow down the closer they got to the hull. With a strong enough charge, they might even be stopped completely and flung in the other direction.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DAL59","CreatedById":180784,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-11-04T13:25:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223210763\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022167158\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221509799788\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002276097\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Diche Bach\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n35 minutes ago, Diche Bach said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n2. How quickly would it need to be recorded to approach any semblance of an \u0022instantaneous\u0022 snapshot\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nArchive\u0027s Wayback Machine already kind of does this.\u00A0\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DAL59","CreatedById":180784,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-11-04T13:46:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf there are 1.28 billion websites, and 2.3 megabytes per page on average, then thee would be about 3 petabytes of data.\u00A0\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://cs.stanford.edu/people/eroberts/courses/soco/projects/1999-00/information-theory/entropy_of_english_9.html\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://cs.stanford.edu/people/eroberts/courses/soco/projects/1999-00/information-theory/entropy_of_english_9.html\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSays that the density of info in written text is 11.8 bits per word.\u00A0 A 100,000 word novel would thus be about 150 kilobytes.\u00A0 20,000,000,000 books would be needed!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou would need to cut down over 322 million trees.\u00A0\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"radonek","CreatedById":84077,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-11-05T07:52:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223210781\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022167158\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221509800835\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022166940\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Earthlinger\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n18 hours ago, Earthlinger said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you could magnetize the hull of a tank so that it had an extremely negative charge, and somehow magnetized incoming bullets so that they acquired a similar negative charge, would this essentially create a sort of repelling-thingy force shield?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe like charges would repel, and the bullets would slow down the closer they got to the hull. With a strong enough charge, they might even be stopped completely and flung in the other direction.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI don\u0027t see why this could not work\u2026 in theory. This is pretty much how electric sails work. One tiny weeny complication is that solar sail works in space and dont need that much charge. Deflecting a projectile would obviously need a lot more and your tank would suck up charge from surroundings so you\u0027d need to replenish it constantly. \u00A0Electron gun would do,\u00A0but I guess that power requirements would be prohibitive. Chargin up incoming projectile could be done with stream of antiprotons. Putting aside power requirements for this, it would also drain you precious charge, because law of charge preservation is a poodle.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOn more, ermmm, positive side, you don\u0027t really need to push as far as stopping incoming projectiles,\u00A0deflecting them \u00A0a bit would be good enough. And if you really are sitting in a tank, you don\u0027t even need to deflect them that much - turning headon hit into glancing blow may be enough.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOf course this is just a thought experiment - with this kind of technology at hand, one would rather pimp up those antiproton accelerators a bit and use them to turn things into hot plasma.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DAL59","CreatedById":180784,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-11-05T16:41:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat if you made a laser out of radio waves?\u00A0\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Steel","CreatedById":49317,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-11-05T16:50:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223211641\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022167158\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221509900082\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022180784\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022DAL59\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n17 minutes ago, DAL59 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat if you made a laser out of radio waves?\u00A0\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.m.wikipedia.org/wiki/Maser\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://en.m.wikipedia.org/wiki/Maser\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#222222;font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\u0022Modern masers can be designed to generate\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0electromagnetic waves at\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#222222;font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\u00A0not only microwave\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0frequencies\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#222222;font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003Ebut also radio and infrared frequencies\u0022\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-11-05T16:59:31Z\u0022 title=\u002211/05/2017 04:59  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003ENovember 5, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by Steel\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DAL59","CreatedById":180784,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-11-05T16:51:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLike low frequency radio waves.\u00A0\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Steel","CreatedById":49317,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-11-05T16:59:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223211648\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022167158\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221509900711\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022180784\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022DAL59\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n7 minutes ago, DAL59 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLike low frequency radio waves.\u00A0\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou\u0027d just have a very large maser essentially\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-11-05T16:59:10Z\u0022 title=\u002211/05/2017 04:59  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003ENovember 5, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by Steel\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"mikegarrison","CreatedById":137807,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-11-05T17:12:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223210781\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022167158\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221509800835\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022166940\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Earthlinger\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 11/4/2017 at 6:07 AM, Earthlinger said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you could magnetize the hull of a tank so that it had an extremely negative charge, and somehow magnetized incoming bullets so that they acquired a similar negative charge, would this essentially create a sort of repelling-thingy force shield?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe like charges would repel, and the bullets would slow down the closer they got to the hull. With a strong enough charge, they might even be stopped completely and flung in the other direction.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat would really suck when your enemies pulled out their positively-charged ammo.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Piatzin","CreatedById":166940,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-11-05T17:12:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223211672\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022167158\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221509901924\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022137807\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022mikegarrison\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, mikegarrison said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat would really suck when your enemies pulled out their positively-charged ammo.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLol yeah \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"MatterBeam","CreatedById":133334,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-11-05T17:58:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223211641\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022167158\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221509900082\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022180784\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022DAL59\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, DAL59 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat if you made a laser out of radio waves?\u00A0\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe RASER.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://goo.gl/aUmzed\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://goo.gl/aUmzed\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Diche Bach","CreatedById":76097,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-11-05T20:27:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat about a \u0022laser\u0022 that involves X-Rays or Gamma Rays? Or Rocks?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nActually, now that I think about it . . .what about a \u0022laser\u0022 that involves melted diamond or something . . . osmium maybe?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n-=-=-this thread needs less skepticism/moderation and more \u0022Absurd Hypothetical questions\u0022\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-11-05T20:29:43Z\u0022 title=\u002211/05/2017 08:29  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003ENovember 5, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by Diche Bach\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003Ehumor\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DDE","CreatedById":146349,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-11-05T21:23:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223211811\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022167158\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221509913676\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002276097\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Diche Bach\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n55 minutes ago, Diche Bach said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat about a \u0022laser\u0022 that involves X-Rays or Gamma Rays?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEasy, relatively speaking - xrasers and grasers are a valid concept. Never heard of a non-consumable graser, but a German-Russian research team in Hamburg already operates a free electron laser that produces x-rays. Both x-rays and gamma rays can be produced by nuclear-bomb-powered designs.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223211811\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022167158\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221509913676\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002276097\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Diche Bach\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n55 minutes ago, Diche Bach said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOr Rocks?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s not a laser. The L constrains it to various forms of electromagnetic radiation.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-11-05T21:23:54Z\u0022 title=\u002211/05/2017 09:23  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003ENovember 5, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by DDE\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Diche Bach","CreatedById":76097,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-11-05T21:27:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223211864\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022167158\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221509917019\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022146349\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022DDE\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJu